                "Formal Register — What to Avoid",
                "<p>Formal letters require a specific register in French. You must use <strong>vous</strong> throughout — never <em>tu</em>. Avoid contractions, slang, and informal connectors like <em>donc</em> at the start of a sentence. Sentences should be complete and well-structured. Passive constructions and impersonal phrases (<em>il est possible de…</em>, <em>il serait souhaitable que…</em>) raise the register. Emotional language should be restrained — state facts and consequences rather than expressing anger.</p>",
                "<ul class=\"slide-list\"><li><strong>Avoid:</strong> <em>tu, t'es, j'veux, truc, super</em></li><li><strong>Use instead:</strong> <em>vous, vous êtes, je souhaite, élément, particulièrement</em></li><li><strong>Avoid:</strong> <em>C'est nul / C'est pas normal</em></li><li><strong>Use instead:</strong> <em>Cette situation est inacceptable / Il est regrettable que…</em></li><li><strong>Avoid:</strong> Short, choppy sentences</li><li><strong>Use instead:</strong> Complex sentences with subordinate clauses</li></ul>"
